# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# What is committed: source + config + templates + tests + docs + openspec.
# What is NOT (this file): the virtualenv, build/cache artifacts, secrets, and
# any *deployed playbook instance* (its wiki/raw/state). Instances are data,
# created per machine/domain with `playmaker init` — keep them OUTSIDE the repo
# (e.g. ~/playbooks/<domain>). See README "What's in version control".
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Python environment & build artifacts
.venv/
venv/
env/
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
build/
dist/
.eggs/

# Test / tooling caches
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.coverage
htmlcov/

# Secrets — never commit a real instance's credentials
.env
**/.env

# Deployed playbook instance data (defensive — instances should live outside
# the repo, but ignore their markers in case one is created in-tree).
# `.openkb/` and `.playmaker/` are unambiguous instance directories.
.openkb/
.playmaker/
# An instance created at the repo root (`playmaker init .`): ignore its wiki +
# raw sources. Anchored to the root so it can't shadow package paths.
/wiki/
/raw/
**/wiki/AGENTS.md.bak

# Local agent/editor config (commit `openspec/`, not this). Delete this line
# if you want to share the OpenSpec slash-commands with collaborators.
.claude/

# Throwaway spike code (validate-before-propose; deleted after).
/spike/

# Local dev notes (machine-specific: test vault path, deploy target). Not shared.
/LOCAL_NOTES.md

# macOS
.DS_Store
